Two primary school children drowned while swimming at Eastern Beach in East London. The boy and a girl aged 13 and 14, were part of a group of  pupils who were pulled  by Buffalo City Metro lifeguards from the water after experiencing difficulty. The minors were part of a group of 26 Grade seven class from Mthatha’s Mbekweni Primary School who visited East London  for a two day  farewell party. Buffalo City Metro spokesperson Samkelo Ngwenya told DispatchLIVE: “Our life guards managed to pull four of the six school kids who were in trouble in the water whilst swimming but, unfortunately for the two, a boy and a girl drowned.” See the full story in DispatchLIVE tomorrow.